<br>
I have not tried to go any further than PoT in PoP just to see what a zone looks like. I am going to ding 55 today, and would like to try PoP for the first time in a group and get some AA exp for the very first time as well. Couls anyone suggest the first spot I should go to and give me some council on PoP? PoT was VERY laggy for me. Do the other zones even out, or can I expect lag everywhere as well?<br>
<br>
I will continue to read the posts and try to find answers that way as well. Comments would be appreciated very much.<br>
<br>
Quipp Bennymaker<br>
55 Mage<br>
(Original Hit and Run Screaming Mage<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :eek --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/eek.gif ALT=":eek"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=stubblekb>StubbleKB</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 83<br> <font color=#333333>(2/6/03 4:05:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=190.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: First time in PoP for a 55 Mage</span><hr size=1> As far as lag goes, in the first tier zones, I found little lag in Disease, Justice and Innovation and moderate lag in Nightmare. Tranquility can be bad depending on where you are.<br>
<br>
Seems to be easiest to get in a group in Nightmare followed by Innovation and Justice. Disease seems to be the hardest.<br>
<br>
I always preferred Disease over the others because the lack of population. I always was able to bring my own group though.<br>
<br>
It's pretty much safe to zone into all of them (unless you happen to zone in while some less than intelligent person is training the zone in point). Probably best to zone in and look around on your own to see how your server population is in each zone.<br>
<br>
One thing I'd recommend is finding the zone out in each of the zones first thing. <p>-Stubble</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=alladdim>alladdim</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 91<br> <font color=#333333>(2/6/03 7:15:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=190.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: First time in PoP for a 55 Mage</span><hr size=1> Lag depends on the time of the day you're playing. There's hardly any lag if you play around 4am - 8am PST (Pacific Time). On the other hand if you play during primetime in the US the lag can hit up to insane levels. Usually PoT has hardly any lag at all. Tier 1 planes have little to no lag. Tier 2-3 planes can get PRETTY VERY crowded during peak hours. Tier 4 planes are usually raid level planes so there aren't too much people XPing in there.<br>
